node.title: Former Man United defender Wootten joins Phoenix for A-League campaign
node.description: The veteran played a handful of games under legendary manager Sir Alex Ferguson.
node.content: ["Veteran defender Scott Wootten - who played four games under legendary manager Sir Alex Ferguson at Manchester United - will join Wellington Phoenix, as they try to resurrect their reeling A-League season.", "Well-travelled Wootten, 30, has played more than 200 games across the various levels of English football, including a handful of appearances at Old Trafford during the icon's final season in charge.", "Most recently, he turned out for third-division Morcambe, before fielding an offer to join the Phoenix, who have lost their last four outings in Australia.", "More to come"]
